# T.I.N.A — Totally Intelligent Neural Assistant

A voice-driven, always-on AI orchestration system. TINA coordinates a team of
specialist agents, keeps persistent memory in an Obsidian vault, runs autonomous
business monitoring, and only interrupts you for decisions that genuinely need you.

Built with Python (FastAPI + WebSockets), a React/Vite dashboard, and Claude.

> **Note on layout:** The live system is the FastAPI backend (`backend/`) plus the
> React dashboard (`frontend/`). The top-level `core/`, `commands/`, and `dashboard/`
> folders and `tina.py` are the **legacy single-process CLI** — kept for reference but
> no longer the entry point.

## Architecture

```
TINA/
├── backend/
│   ├── main.py              # ENTRY POINT — FastAPI app, WebSocket server,
│   │                        #   all autonomous schedulers, Slack listener
│   └── tina/
│       ├── agent.py         # Tina — the orchestrator (Claude Sonnet 4.6)
│       ├── agent_state.py   # background agent dispatch + state
│       ├── memory.py        # Obsidian vault memory writer
│       ├── memory_db.py     # Supabase conversation persistence
│       ├── diagnostics.py   # startup health checks
│       ├── wake_word.py     # faster-whisper wake-word detector (off by default)
│       └── agents/
│           ├── base.py      # BaseAgent — shared tool loop + compaction
│           ├── coding.py    # Sam     — code, debug, architecture
│           ├── research.py  # Charlie — web/news/wiki research, media
│           ├── email.py     # Tristan — Gmail + Outlook, triage, drafts
│           ├── data.py      # Connor  — CSV/Excel/JSON, charts, financials
│           ├── marketing.py # Wade    — social content, Meta posting
│           ├── website.py   # Jamie   — UI/UX, HTML/CSS/JS, React/Next.js
│           └── pm.py        # Morgan  — project manager / agent coordinator
├── tools/                   # Tool modules (auto-discovered: DEFINITIONS + handle)
│   ├── vault.py  weather.py  calendar_tool.py  github_tool.py  slack_tool.py
│   ├── stripe_tool.py  kaos_tool.py  social_tool.py  gdrive_tool.py
│   ├── filesystem_tool.py  git_tool.py  test_tool.py  lint_tool.py
│   ├── screenshot_tool.py  commission_tool.py  data_tool.py  docs_tool.py …
├── frontend/                # React + Vite dashboard (TinaFace, agent grid, logs)
├── scripts/                 # auth_gmail / auth_calendar / imports / utilities
├── config.py                # ALL settings — models, paths, voices, system prompt
├── data/                    # runtime state (tokens, monitor state, status) — gitignored
└── docker-compose.yml       # (Postgres/Redis — optional)
```

## The agents

| Agent   | Name    | Owns |
|---------|---------|------|
| coding    | **Sam**     | Code, debugging, architecture, self-development |
| research  | **Charlie** | Web/news/Wikipedia research, downloads media |
| email     | **Tristan** | Gmail + Outlook, triage, drafts (never auto-sends) |
| data      | **Connor**  | CSV/Excel/JSON analysis, financials, charts |
| marketing | **Wade**    | Social content, trends, Facebook/Instagram posting |
| website   | **Jamie**   | UI/UX, HTML/CSS/JS, React/Next.js, SEO |
| pm        | **Morgan**  | Coordinates a project brief → completion across agents |

Tina delegates to specialists via `delegate_to_agent` (background, non-blocking).
Morgan drives specialists via `commission_agent` with a critical PASS / NEEDS-MORE-WORK
review gate. Agents communicate through Slack channels and the shared Obsidian vault.

## What runs automatically

Scheduled in the backend lifespan (`backend/main.py`):

- **Morning briefing** — once/day on first startup: opens Calendar, pushes
  weather / calendar / Stripe / KAOS cards, then speaks a synthesized summary.
- **Weekly briefing** (Mon) — Connor + Wade + Tristan produce a business report.
- **Email triage** (8am, 2pm) — Tristan classifies, files, and drafts replies.
- **Inbox pipeline** (15 min) — classifies vault `00-Inbox/` notes and routes them.
- **KAOS monitor** (15 min) — tickets, signups, subscriptions, Sentry errors.
- **Stripe monitor** (30 min) — failed charges, subs, disputes, live MRR.
- **Pattern scan** (Sun) — Connor mines KAOS tickets for feature-request signals.
- **Nightly reindex** (2am) — Sam rebuilds each project's codebase index.

## Voice & I/O

- **STT:** Deepgram nova-2 (en-AU) by default; faster-whisper offline fallback.
- **TTS:** ElevenLabs (Matilda, raw PCM); pyttsx3 local fallback.
- **Input:** browser mic via spacebar push-to-talk, text bar, or Slack DM.
- **Wake word** is disabled by default — holding the mic open continuously triggered
  system-wide audio AEC artifacts. Set `WAKE_WORD_ENABLED=true` only if your hardware
  handles it cleanly.

## Setup

### 1. Install dependencies
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
cd frontend && npm install
```

### 2. Create your `.env` (in the repo root)
```
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=...
ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=...
TAVILY_API_KEY=...
OPENWEATHER_API_KEY=...
GITHUB_TOKEN=...
SUPABASE_URL=...           SUPABASE_KEY=...
SLACK_TINA_BOT_TOKEN=...   SLACK_APP_TOKEN=...   SLACK_CHANNEL=...   SLACK_KY_USER_ID=...
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=...
KAOS_SUPABASE_URL=...      KAOS_SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY=...
SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN=...      SENTRY_ORG=...        SENTRY_PROJECT=...
META_PAGE_ACCESS_TOKEN=... META_PAGE_ID=...      META_INSTAGRAM_ACCOUNT_ID=...
WAKE_WORD_ENABLED=false
# KLJ_BASE=C:\Users\...\Desktop\KLJ   (override on a different machine)
```

### 3. Google auth (Calendar + Gmail)
Place OAuth `credentials.json` in the root, then:
```bash
python scripts/auth_calendar.py
python scripts/auth_gmail.py
```

### 4. Run
```bash
# Backend (from repo root)
python -m uvicorn backend.main:app --port 8000

# Frontend (second terminal)
cd frontend && npm run dev
```

Open the Vite dev URL the frontend prints. Hold **spacebar** to talk.

## Extending TINA

- **New tool** — add a file in `tools/` with a `DEFINITIONS` list and a
  `handle(name, inputs)` function, then include the module in the relevant agent's
  `tool_modules`. Tina's own tools are wired in `backend/main.py` / `agent.py`.
- **New agent** — subclass `BaseAgent` in `backend/tina/agents/`, set `name`,
  `description`, `system`, and `tool_modules`, and register it in the dispatch map.

## Config

All settings live in `config.py` — models, vault/sites paths, voices, the project
registry, and the full system prompt. Change things there, not in individual modules.
Models: `claude-sonnet-4-6` (orchestrator + agents), `claude-opus-4-8` (complex tasks),
`claude-haiku-4-5` (inbox classification).
